race.comment: THE BOSS MAN (2) went forward last start over 1350m at Ipswich and held on well for third, beaten a neck. Looks well placed so expect another big run. THE IMMORTALS (6) accounted for a maiden field over 1200m at Kilcoy last start, finishing a head ahead of the nearest rival. Re-unites with Brandon Lerena who was on board last start. Looms as one of the hardest to beat again. AIMA SUN (8) peaked on her run when resuming last start over 1010m at Murwillumbah, winding up in fourth. Usually performs well with that run under her belt and rates among the leading chances. UCELLE (13) ran a strong race last time out, finishing fourth and beaten only 2 lengths over 1300m at Sunshine Coast. Best figures measure up and is set to run well again.
